<collectorName box="[294,362,1140,1165]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Based</collectorName>
on these differences (variety of the coloration of the pronotum) 
<collectorName box="[1085,1354,1140,1165]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Brunner von Wattenwyl</collectorName>
(1882) describes 
<taxonomicName authority="Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1865" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1865" box="[266,687,1176,1200]" class="Insecta" family="Ectobiidae" genus="Aphlebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="marginata" variety="erythronota">
<emphasis box="[266,494,1176,1200]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Aphlebia marginata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[556,687,1176,1200]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">erythronota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Drenski" box="[749,923,1175,1200]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" refString="Drenski, P. (1939) Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Schaben (Blattoidea) in Bulgarien. Mitteilungen der Bulgarischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft in Sofia, 8, 1 - 10. [in Bulgarian]" type="journal article" year="1939">
<collectorName box="[749,838,1175,1200]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Drenski</collectorName>
(1939)
</bibRefCitation>
describes 
<taxonomicName authority="Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1865" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1865" box="[1049,1428,1176,1200]" class="Insecta" family="Ectobiidae" genus="Aphlebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="marginata" subSpecies="meridionalis">
<emphasis box="[1049,1428,1176,1200]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Aphlebia marginata meridionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<collectorName box="[151,210,1213,1236]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Later</collectorName>
on, the latter is synonymized (Harz &amp; Kaltenbach 1 976) but still 
<taxonomicName authority="Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1865" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1865" box="[1028,1404,1212,1236]" class="Insecta" family="Ectobiidae" genus="Aphlebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="marginata" subSpecies="erythronota">
<emphasis box="[1028,1404,1212,1236]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Aphlebia marginata erythronota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered a valid taxon (according to the 
<collectionCode box="[704,769,1248,1272]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">ICZN</collectionCode>
Article 45.6.3-4. 1999) (
<bibRefCitation author="Beccaloni" box="[1092,1284,1247,1272]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" refString="Beccaloni, G. W. (2016) Cockroach Species File Online. Version 5.0 / 5.0. World Wide Web electronic publication. Available from: http: // Cockroach. SpeciesFile. org (accessed 28 April 2016)" type="journal article" year="2016">Beccaloni 2016</bibRefCitation>
), though its conspecificity with 
<taxonomicName authority="Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1865" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1865" box="[372,406,1284,1308]" class="Insecta" family="Ectobiidae" genus="Aphlebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis box="[372,406,1284,1308]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">
<collectingCountry box="[372,406,1284,1308]" name="Philippines" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Ph</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</materialsCitation>
. marginata has already been proposed (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Beccaloni" box="[896,1076,1284,1309]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" refString="Beccaloni, G. W. (2016) Cockroach Species File Online. Version 5.0 / 5.0. World Wide Web electronic publication. Available from: http: // Cockroach. SpeciesFile. org (accessed 28 April 2016)" type="journal article" year="2016">Beccaloni 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Herewith, we comply with the latter statement and regard 
<taxonomicName authority="Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1865" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1865" box="[455,817,1320,1344]" class="Insecta" family="Ectobiidae" genus="Aphlebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="marginata" subSpecies="erythronota">
<emphasis box="[455,817,1320,1344]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Aphlebia marginata erythronota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1865" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1865" box="[1189,1350,1320,1344]" class="Insecta" family="Ectobiidae" genus="Aphlebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis box="[1189,1350,1320,1344]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Ph. marginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="357" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1103,1560]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,504,1356,1381]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">
Distribution in 
<collectingCountry box="[383,487,1356,1381]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
(
</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[505,585,1356,1381]" captionStart="FIGURE 79" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1989,2011]" captionTargetBox="[178,1387,1127,1954]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[178,1388,1127,1955]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 79. Distribution of Phyllodromica marginata and Phyllodromica pulcherrima in Bulgaria." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264838/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Fig. 79</figureCitation>
): Distributed in the lowlands of southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1059,1156,1356,1381]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
and along the Black Sea coast up to 
<quantity box="[282,354,1391,1416]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" unit="m" value="600.0">600 m</quantity>
altitude. Inhabits the soil and leaf litter of xerothermic oak forests as well as open stony karstic habitats.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
